# Reference for the Release and Packaging workflows' configuration. All secrets
# are set under repo Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions — this file only
# documents their names (never their values).
#
# The release builds are intentionally UNSIGNED — this project does not use paid
# code-signing certificates (see docs/RELEASE.md), so the release pipeline needs
# no Apple or Windows signing/notarization secrets. Its only credential is
# GITHUB_TOKEN, which GitHub Actions provides automatically.
#
# If code signing is ever adopted, the Apple/Windows certificate secret names
# would be documented here — and wired into the tauri-action step in
# .github/workflows/release.yml.
#
# --- Packaging (.github/workflows/packaging.yml) — see docs/packaging.md ---
# Publishing to the AUR and the Homebrew tap needs two secrets:
#
#   AUR_SSH_PRIVATE_KEY  Private half of the dedicated ed25519 keypair whose
#                        public half is registered on the AUR account. Pushes the
#                        unplot-bin package over ssh://aur@aur.archlinux.org.
#
#   HOMEBREW_TAP_TOKEN   Fine-grained PAT scoped to vitorwilson/homebrew-unplot
#                        only, Contents: Read and write. Pushes Casks/unplot.rb to
#                        the tap (GITHUB_TOKEN cannot push to another repo).
